We sat for 45 minutes waiting for our food (Side salad, JD burger, & JD chicken sandwich) while we watched her continuously walk by us without her acknowledging us. Not even so much as a table touch and \xe2\x80\x9cit\xe2\x80\x99ll just be a few minutes\xe2\x80\x9d. status_message: b"I was really disappointed with my meal doing my family outing at TGIF 12811 S tryon st. charlotte nc 2827 on Saturday January 20th.  I ordered jack Daniel ribs that was dry and meatless (Mostly bones) I had to ask the waitress for more sauce and after realizing there was more bones then meats I ask to order something else.  She came back to the table to tell me her manager would cook me a few more ribs because I was not happy with my order.  She also informed me he was coming out to talk to me. The restaurant was understaff so I had to ask the waitress where was my ribs?  She said oh, I thought they brought them out. I told her to forget it just bring us the ticket.  She express how sorry she was and that the manager would come out and talk with me.  I told her that's the second time she said that and he hasn't come out yet.  My husband informed me his food was not good either.  We have been to TGIF many times but was really disappointed in the service and the food.  You could tell a lot of other customers felt the same way we did.   We don't eat out a lot because I am a family of 5 and the cost can get expensive, but when I do I don't like giving my money away.  Sometimes restaurants need to regroup and provide on-going training for their employees or maybe give incentives to improve their services.  I literally felt like I gave my money away!!!!!!!!!!!!"

b'I want to take just a couple minutes of your time and bring your attention to the gentleman in the red shirt below. My boyfriend and I decide to go out to dinner (like we normally do almost every other weekend or so). Well that nights choice for restaurants was TGI Friday\'s here in Anchorage, Alaska. Anyways so we go in and are instantly greeted by a wonderful crew of people. After just a couple minutes of sitting down me and my boyfriend notice this Guy in the red shirt just walking all over the place. After a couple of minutes of watching him we figured out that he had to be the manager of the place. After we made that conclusion we thought "oh he\'s probably just out for a couple minutes to see how everything is and then he\'ll go back to his office and hide." Boy were we TOTALLY WRONG!! Not only was he out on the floor for the hour and half we were there but he also did so many things. He was constantly helping his crew with things like serving people, taking plates away, seeing if you need anything, getting drinks, and even (gasp) cleaning and wiping down tables. There were also many times he went into the kitchen and I can only imagine what he was helping his chefs with back there. Anyways the point of this post is to bring to light what an amazing Manager this gentleman is. We live in a world were most people when they get promoted or move up they forget where they came from and thank that they are better/above there employees. But not this guy, he truly shined that night when we were there, not because he is better then his crew/employees but for the exact opposite! He was doing everything that he expects his employees to do, and he did them right along side with them. That my friends is a TRUE MANAGER!! Please if you stop in to TGI Friday\'s in Anchorage give this man a hand shake and a pat on the back for not letting his title as manager go to his head and for all his hard work. \n\nThank you again Dyan (that\'s the red shirt manager) for the best dining experience I have ever. I will definitely be coming back!'

b'Today, I went to the TGI Fridays at 47 Broadway in lower Manhattan, NY at 4PM. The person attending us would not accept the valid temporary NYS drivers license, even though I showed her another valid picture ID. She became very rude and increasingly hostile toward me. I started to record the situation and asked her for her name so that I could go to the GM and explain how rude she was being to the management. As I asked her for her name she smacked and scratched me on the face and almost knocked my phone out of my hand.  I called the police and made a report of assault.  When I finally spoke to the manager, they made light of the situation as if it was nothing.  As I was outside, I asked a crew member what her name was and he told me it was Mary. b"I apologize resorting to this, but I tried 3 other ways of contacting someone regarding our service tonight at Friday's. 

   I want to start by saying, our waitress Madison, was very friendly and she cannot be held solely responsible for our terrible experience. 

  My husband and I received a gift card as a gift for dog sitting. We generally do not come to Friday's but was excited to have a nice dinner. Or so we thought. 

  My husband ordered the turkey burger which we come to find out was no longer on the menu. Bummer. So he ordered something else along with an app. I ordered the salmon with lobster and requested no Alfredo sauce since I'm lactose intolerant. I still wanted mushrooms, so Madison explained I could get mushrooms, they would just be cooked separately. Totally cool. My sides were broccoli and a salad. I also added a side of 5 shrimp. 

   When our app came, it was great. However when our food arrived, we were so disappointed. No salad, no mushrooms and no shrimp! To boot, the portion I received was pitiful. They should be ashamed to send this out for $17. I took a photo which I attached below.

   Madison retrieved everything I was missing and apologized. She did not charge me for the shrimp because of the mistake. I was so hungry I ate my food, and we asked for the bill. 

  When the bill came I saw that she charged me for the mushroom. Which was a surprise to me, considering if I wasn't lactose intolerant they would have come free. Then I notice I'm charged for a 3rd rum and coke from the bar in which I did not have. I only drank 2. I brought it to her attention and she took it off stating that there had been 3 because someone knocked my 2nd out of her hand on the way to our table and she forgot to remove it. That could explain why it took so long to receive. 

   I understand it was a busy Friday night but as you'll see below, the standards are clearly under expectations and Friday's really needs to take a look at what the kitchen is serving people (especially for the high prices you have!)"

b'Dear Fridays,

I want to tell you about the amazing cajun chicken pasta I had for dinner tonight. 

I want to, but I can't.

You might be wondering why. You see, I tried to go to dinner tonight with my fiance at the Friday's on Anton Blvd in Costa Mesa, California. I don't know if you live near, or have ever been in, southern California, but the weather is wonderful. It was 73 degrees this evening around 8:30.

We wanted to have dinner on the patio. When we got there, we waited a couple minutes -- not an unreasonable amount of time, but a short while (this will become relevant in a moment) -- to see a hostess. When we requested outdoor seating, we were told that there was no outdoor seating available because the space was too tight for the server to fit through as there was a large party seated there. 

We were told that we had the option to "wait for a table, I guess... but it will probably be a while..." I don't know if she was tired, or bored, or just didn't want us to choose to do that, but it sounded like she didn't really want us to take her up on it. 

We looked at each other, confused, because we had seen a likely looking table when we walked passed the patio. We mentioned there was a table that didn't seem restricted, but the hostess hadn't bothered to actually check -- and she repeated that there was no available seating outside.

As we walked out, I wondered why the hostess hadn't even bothered to check. My fiance and I stopped and looked at each other, wondering what to do, as we stared at the empty table in the far corner that I had been eyeing on the way in, which was in no way blocked or cramped by the large party. 

We debated going back in and asking for the table in the corner, the one that was next to the door, that had the same access and room around it as every other time we've ever been to Fridays when no large party was present, that didn't require squeezing by any parties, large or otherwise, but ultimately decided that we didn't want to tell the hostess how to do her job and potentially risk frosty service.  

We both felt it was a really awkward position to put potential customers in, telling us that something was not available when it was obvious that A, it was, B, the hostess had no way to know if that was true as tables leave all the time and the front was empty when we arrived, and C, she didn't bother to check.

The next time I want to pay $15 for pasta I guess we'll just go to the cheesecake factory.

Sincerely, 

A very disappointed woman who ate a burger for dinner'

b"Friday night I went out to eat in celebration of my sister's High School graduation. We ate at T.G.I Friday's in Green Acres Mall and our waiter was nothing less than amazing. He took the large order for our drinks, appetizers and lastly our meals in that order since we were a large party. Everything came quickly but our drinks took forever. When they finally came, one of the alcoholic beverages were too dark as if a darker liquid fell into it but our amazing waiter fixed it with no problem. The rest of dinner was great until I got a little further into drinking my mango passion smoothie and realized there was a piece of bacon in my drink, at least that's what I thought it was. After further analyzing it we came to the conclusion that it was a band-aid. \nAfter speaking to the manager he told me that he checked in with the barista and that the band-aid never came into direct contact with his skin or the actual cut. He explained to me that the actual cut was on his finger which was covered by a band-aid, a finger cot and a glove in that order. He said that the barista chose to put an extra band-aid on the outside of the glove to keep the original band-aid in place, which doesn't make any sense. Eventually I asked to see the barista's hand for myself and they escorted me to go look. They told me he was in the bathroom but as I was standing there I noticed that none of the employees behind the counter working the bar didn't have any gloves on their hands. He then came back to me 2 minutes later to say that he was no longer in the building because his shift was over at 4pm yet it was minutes until 5pm. Eventually the Assistant General Manager came out and spoke with me but I was never able to actually see his hand myself. This is very unsanitary and unacceptable. I filled out a store complaint and was told I would get a phone call within 24-48 hours it's now Tuesday and I haven't received any phone calls from anyone. I have the risk of catching Hepatitis C and no one has called me yet about this incident. I'm currently at the doctor waiting to get blood work done because of this bandaid I found. I should be at work right now and I can't be there because of negligence and unprofessionalism."

b"So I've just taken the kids to TGI's and all I can say is amazing . As anyone who's been to TGI's knows it's loud and busy and for any autistic person it's a sensory overload waiting to happen I was weary of taking Lucy but I decided to try . I requested at table by the window on my booking knowing it was better for Lucy , I crossed my fingers and off we went we arrived and as requested we had a table by the window , good start now time to see how Lucy handles it . The next thing I know we are greeted by our waitress Lara . Not only did she engage with Lucy , but for the first time in a long while Lucy had a conversation with a complete stranger!  yes it was about a burger but there was eye contact and Lucy was Lucy not mirroring some thing she had seen .She knelt next to the table to take our order , for those of you that no Lucy she struggles with people looming above her and starts to panic . I don't even think Lara knew what she had done, she brought Lucy stickers and got Jacob and Lucy laughing and giggling .  She made the whole visit a pleasurable one  and I even stopped watching Lucy for signs of a meltdown . And I spent time on a night out chatting with Jacob this never happens and as Lucy's brother he is used to and happy to put Lucy first but tonight we had a good chat . I would recommend TGI'S to anyone this was a breath of fresh air . Thank you TGI Fridays and thank you Lara you made tonight a dream  . #TGIfridays #amazing #autism #adhd"

Below my comment to the restaurant in Spanish, so please you can forward to them:\n\n"Acabamos de tener una desagradable experiencia en Friday\'s del Boulevard Moraz\xc3\xa1n. Pedimos dos ensaladas y la ensalada de Luis tra\xc3\xada un extra de cabello humano. Cuando le dijimos a la mesera ella s\xc3\xb3lo ofreci\xc3\xb3 cambiarnos la ensalada o pedir alg\xc3\xban otro plato del men\xc3\xba. b"On April 14 while attending a conference in Louisville, KY two friends and I decided to go to the TGI Fridays on 4th #1108. We arrived around 10pm. We sat in the bar area at one of the high tops. The hostess came over to let us know our server would be over shortly.  Within a few moments he came over. We asked for three waters and three beers. The waters came immediately. 30 minutes later the beers came.  We soon realized that our waiter was taking care of the entire bar area and the bar tender was taking care of peope at the bar.  So we moved to the bar thinking the service would be better.  So we placed our order. Avis Criss Gordon ordered the Sizzlin Chicken, Tyrone ordered the Cheeseburger and I ordered the Chicken Tenders.  40 minutes later our food arrived. The French Fries were cold and the Tenders were under cooked and the Sizzling Chicken had sizzled out, burned, and cold. When I brought this to the bar tenders attention his response was i didn't cook it nor did i serve it, I just took your order.  WHAT??? We couldn't believe what we had just heard and witnessed. The MOD came over and apologize and attempt to make things right by taking care our meal. Just know We will Never Ever step foot in another TGI Fridays."

b'Tired of \xe2\x80\x9cdining al desko\xe2\x80\x9d?  It\xe2\x80\x99s time to take back your lunch break! On Wednesday April 13th TGI Fridays is declaring it National Make Lunch Count Day to give more power to your lunch hour. More and more Americans are forgoing their lunch breaks each day to keep up with their busy schedules. This has led to a pandemic that is sweeping our nation: FOLO, the Fear of Lunching Out. 

So grab your friends or your work buds and fight the FOLO by visiting select TGI Friday\xe2\x80\x99s locations on April 13th to participate National Make Lunch Count Day. Long live the lunch hour!

Info at bit.ly/makelunchcount'

b'Downloaded your app for andriod and was pleasantly surprised when it said that you could get a free appetiser and 2 for 1 cocktails so thought that I would go for dinner with my girlfriend and redeem these great offers only to be told that they are not valid in Scotland. I am highly dissapointed that it only states in the terms and conditions state that it is only not valid in Northern Ireland but says nothing about Scotland but we were refused the use of the offers in the app in store. I feel that this is very miss leading to the consumer and wonder how many other patrons have been refused the offer when the terms and conditions clearly state that it is only Northern Ireland that it does not appy to. Not only this but when our paid for appetiser arrived there were no forks to eat it with and we had to wait 5 minutes before a waitress would come over and give us 2 forks so we could share the appetiser while it was going cold.

We both have been avid fans of TGI Fridays for years and have spent a small fortune in your various stores accross the UK but this visit has left a particularly bitter taste in our mouths.

Kind regards

Stuart'

b"Steve, Manager of the Woodlands, Texas store,

We spoke today about your 30.06 policy that  puts all our lives I danger when you force clients to leave their legally owned arms in their cars. 

I am an Honorably Discharged Navy Veteran  and have had my CHL for over 6 years.   

I am at Chili's having lunch with my wife.  The do not have a 30.06 OR a 30.07 sign. 

I have been a loyal customer  of Fridays
for  as long as I can remember your location being  there. I will never return. 

I cut my Friday's gift card in half and made a video which I will share with all my family, friends, co-workers, my Facebook page, my Facebook friends, Chili's Facebook page AND Friday's Facebook page. 

Your decision has no basis in fact.  FBI statistics show that every state that has CHLs have lower gun violent than every state that does not. 

Until Jan, 2016 Texas was among only 7 states that banned open carry.  

The country  didn't become the Wild West.  Innocent bystanders were not slaughtered. 

I understand  banishing open carry.  I DO NOT when it comes to my 2nd amendment rights to protect myself and the cautious  use of my CHL. 

Do not underestimate the CHL lobby.  

Sent from Frank's iPhone"

b'TGI Fridays

I placed a to-go order for green bean fries at TGI Fridays in DFW airport on 12/24. This is how the box looked like when I opened the lid. I am very disappointed that huge restaurant chain is using these kind of Styrofoam containers to serve hot food to customers. Customers order food, not food blended with melted Styrofoam.

I have shown this to the manager on shift at the time and he told me that Styrofoam was the only container that TGI Fridays uses to serve food to-go. He was nice enough to issue me a refund in this case. But it doesn\xe2\x80\x99t solve the problem of thousands of other customers picking up hot food in these Styrofoam containers from your restaurants. Please invest some time and money in understanding the dangers of serving hot food in Styrofoam containers. I hope to see your restaurant using safer containers to serve hot food by putting customers\xe2\x80\x99 health as a priority and making an example for other restaurants to follow.'

b"Went to your store 0119 and had the worst experience ever! First your hostesses were to busy talking to hold the doors open to anyone coming in or out. They just kept chatting. Then they argued who would get the phone instead of assist the guest lining up. There were only 4-6 tables full in the whole restaurant and when I said I needed a table for 1 they said oh it will be 5-10 minute wait. When I asked why they said we don't have enough servers. They suggested that I go to the bar which I explained I couldn't sit at the bar stools since I am 9 months pregnant. They just laughed and started talking about how crazy that was. Stood there for 20 minutes and they seated people who came in after me. When I asked how much longer it was going to take they seated me right away. First the hostss took me to a table and the other hostess came up to her and said no not there, the other table which was all the way on the opposite side of the restaurant. Sat down, waited 5-10 minutes for my server to come. I ordered a water and then the appetizer where you pick 3 of the choices. When it came out my wings weren't fully done and the cheese sticks were over cooked to where all the cheese exploded out of them. There was absolutely no manager on the floor to take any complaints. It was ridiculous. I used to work at a Fridays, I don't know if the policy has changed to where you have to have a manager on the floor or if the hostesses don't have to greet people anymore but I dont think I will ever go to Fridays again."

b"Good evening,

I've left my share of negative reviews because of horrible experiences in the past although this evening was different in every single way imaginable. The restaurant was very chaotic tonight but it was a controlled chaotic if that makes any sense. Our waitress this evening was Katrina.....(Bensalem, PA) we've had her in the past and have been pleased but tonight was just exceptional. She's nice, observant, personable, energetic, kind,.respectful, knowledgeable......I really could keep going on! Not only was she great but everything about the food was great as well! The presentation was even amazing and honestly that usually lacks big time here. I enjoyed her service as well as the experience and that's why I gave her close to a 100% tip. Plus a little Merry Christmas. \xf0\x9f\x98\x89 People like her are really hard to come by and I really hope she's recognized for providing such great service.

Thank you"

status_message: b'After spending all day at Disney we were starving and ready to eat. It was about 7:30 on a Wednesday, so it wasn\'t busy at all. Our server finally came to our table, he was so fast that if my boyfriend hadn\'t stopped him he would have already walked away without our app order. After waiting for a good 15 min on nachos the plate came out. What a sad excuse for a nacho that has ever been seen on earth. Hard taco shells cut it half with refried beans and I guess you could say there was beef on there, with shredded cheese that was microwaved on. I could have made better nachos out of dog food. Thankfully our entr\xc3\xa9es came out right after we finished our food, but I think that\'s because it had been sitting in the window in the kitchen the entire time. I asked for my burger to be pink in the middle, it was well done. And cold. And  fries tasted like they were from this morning. What really cracked me up was when our server placed the dessert menu on our table and said "just in case". Ha. I will never be back to this place.'

Please post this Letter to ALL their Facebook Pages!

To all Executives and Upper Management,
 Please know, this letter is to get a policy enacted, it is NOT AN ACCUSATION, as we are certain that the majority of restaurants support the Law Enforcement and Veteran communities. Unfortunately, in recent weeks, we have become aware of Employees and Management of many 'fast food' stores disrespecting Police Officers and Veterans in uniform by writing notes on food packaging and verbally refusing service to Police Officers and Veterans while on duty and in uniform. In addition, your attorneys should brief you on the Law Enforcement Officers Safety Act, which in effect, allows an on-duty officer to open carry in any place that it is not prohibited or restricted on government property. All your employees should be made aware of this law! As Americans, and Veterans, we stand with millions of Americans who see this behavior as unacceptable! We are requesting that all fast food and dine in chains send memos to all store Managers, Employees and Franchise Owners, and adopt a company policy of immediate dismissal of any Employee found to have committed this discrimination or harassment. Our goal, is only to get cooperation, but as we have seen, such incidents can lead to Boycotts and Nationwide outrage. We would like to think that the customers who support your business are ALL important to you. Those who put their lives on the line for our safety and freedom deserve respect from all who live under the veil of their bravery and sacrifice. We are requesting a response to let us know that you have addressed this issue, and that your employees have been informed of your policy, or change in policy...Thank you Sincerely for your cooperation in this matter.
 Your Customers"

b'I dont know where to begin on describing my most unpleasant visit to T.G.I. Friday\'s. Yesterday, I went with a work group to go to a Friday\'s that we regularly frequent. It began when the waitress was told that we had FREE Appetizer coupons. That\'s when she told us it\'d be $8.00 off of an appetizer....the coupon said FREE....but we didn\'t argue and just tried to use the coupons to the most. When I realized my appetizer wouldn\'t be free I asked about the Endless Appetizer which runs $12/$13. The waitress told me that if I were to order that, $8.00 would be taken off the regular price of the first one and afterwards I would be charged the normal price for each refill/order. Of course that didn\'t make sense to me if the Endless appetizer promo is only $12/$13. So I didn\'t dwell on that and decided to go with the Take 3 another appetizer deal. Since I am allergic to pork, I asked if I could get mozzarella sticks and double wings. She then told me that I would not be able to double. Then she said certain pork made dishes could be altered to not have the pork in it. However, to avoid an allergic reaction to this insult being called "service",  I just ordered a Caesar salad and some wings. As I waited forever for my food, I sipped my beverage down and hoped to be topped off but to no avail, I was sipping melted ice. Then I noticed the group I was with who ordered well done steaks, burgers, and meals that take longer to cook than mine all got their meals before me! I was the last to get my burnt, tiger-striped, dry wings and salad with rotten lettuce. There was literally lettuce in my Caesar salad that was whitish-brown. datbglaze@gmail.com'

b'Coming from the wife of a police officer, this is terribly disappointing. "...with all the public shootings, we just want to do our best to keep all the guest safe...".  Yet you ask officers to leave?  Also, I know misunderstandings happen but it doesn\'t make much sense to ask any uniformed officer to leave a place of business no matter what the reason.  It\'s frustrating when you see people you love risking their lives for others and then be treated in this manner.  Whether or not your establishment supports our men and women in blue, some of your employees do not. I can speak for many LEO families when I say we don\'t visit where we aren\'t welcome.'

b'I am including a pic of an apology posted by the Franklin Tennessee Friday\'s. Obviously by someone that had posting rights. A responsible manager, if bold enough to ask the officers to leave, should have simply asked for proper identification. I wouldn\'t eat at any Friday\'s "to make it right" as the Franklin Friday\'s posted. Yeh they\'ll make it "right". I would be afraid the food would be tainted. status_message:
b"The wife and i met at Fridays in Brooklyn, OH friday evening (9/4/15). She met me at 5:45pm. When she showed up, i had her favorite appetizer on the table. We ordered dinner at 5:55. We each got the Jack D sirloin and i paired mine with Jack ribs.

At 6:35, our meals finally showed up. Our medium steaks were between Medium -well and over -well-done. 30 seconds after we got the plates, one of the three bartenders taking care of us checked on us. That's  when we cut into the shoe leather that used to be steaks. The individual offered to have them recooked but we were extremely hungry and didnt want to wait another half hour. He offered to tell the manager. 

She showed up a few minutes later. She offered to take the costs of the indvidual steaks off of our bill and send us home with desserts.

That was nice, but we were already going to be using a BOGO entree coupon, so what savings was there for us when she told us to keep that coupon because we would probably be saving more with the discounted steaks? (Note : we did... by about 3 cents). 

I sent my wife home after we ordered our takeout desserts at 7pm. I was finally able to leave at 730 after i finally received the desserts and the adjusted check. I also noticied that our 2 non alcoholic drinks and appetizer were removed from the check as well. That was appreciated. 

That being said, I'm not looking for anything in compensation.  I want to point out the long wait we had for dinner as well as the half hour inhad to wait for the desserts that were supposed to be a compensation themselves for a long wait and poor food quality. Why wasnt more emphasis placed on making sure my table was better taken care of after having already suffered? 

The final straw was when we opened my wifes dessert ... the salted caramel dessert. See the attached picture ... it is sitting in  a 6x6 box ... it looks positively miniscule.

We have had very few bad experiences at this location. This might have been our first one. However,  attention needed to be called to it."

b'Usually.. Im a huge fan of TGIS.. Crispy noodle salad and a nice drink. Its an odd treat which we really enjoy.. Not today.
To say the service was appalling is an understatement.
We were waiting almost ten minutes for a table in an almost empty restauraunt.. Initially looking like the waiter was dealing with a customer at the till, and it becoming fast apparent he was actually using it for a bit of a flirt with a girl.
We ended up beong seated by the bar waitress.. 
At this point there was one family behind us and the two girls at a other table the waiter was "dealing with" ... Leaning across the table not only looked unprofessional but made it clear he was not interested in any other clientele.
15 minutes we waited for him to take our order..not once did he leave the girls table.drinks orders which from past experience from tgis are given before meal werent even offered... He finally took our order and went straight back to the girls table. Our food ended up being taken out by another waiter, who was working hard as it was cleaning his own section. 
Its apparent we werent the only ones with this poor service as the family behind us explicitly discussed with each other how they would not be tipping the waiter... Only the fact my partner and I were so hungry we would of got up and left... 

Infact.... He was there so long we were even able to snap a picture. I have no problem with staff having a chat with customers coming from a retail background, but this is not the service we know from TGIs but it has greatly put us off going again.'

b'So we have coming to the same Friday\'s for years and haven\'t been in a while. Craving potato skins and seeing the ad for endless apps, we decided to come eat dinner here. When we received the potato skins, I noticed the cheese wasn\'t melting like normal cheese and there was an oily quality to them. Biting into the potato skins, the "cheese" had a very powdery texture inside which fell apart in my mouth. Normally the cheese has a melted and oozing texture, but this tasted like a sort of fake cheese product. I tried to continue eating it but I could not get over the texture and we chose not to eat the rest of it. We didn\'t complain at the restaurant because judging by your advertising photos in the menu, this is the quality you plan to provide to customers. I would have to say I am disappointed that you would choose to downgrade the quality of your food items. It will be quite some time before we return, if we do return.'

status_message: b"Tonight we visited your Aberdeen Beach branch. What an amazing experience! It was our daughters birthday, we were immediately, warmly greeted at the door, shown to our table and the cake we had brought discreetly taken to the kitchen. Within a few minutes our waiter appeared and introduced himself, spoke about the menu and told us he would be back in a few minutes for our drinks order. For the whole evening he was always on hand for anything we needed, service was quick and flawless, without even having to ask he brought my drink refill, he entertained our two daughters with balloons whilst we got a chance to eat and then brought staff over to sing happy birthday to our wee girl. Really, truly was outstanding service! Sadly I didn't catch his name before we left but I did get a snap of him making the girls balloons! Keep up the great work TGIs! We will be back! Thanks!"

b'This foul pile of mush was what was delivered when I ordered "Steamed Broccoli."  The waiter defended it with, "Well, that's the way it's been all week!"  He offered to let me allow my mashed potatoes and steak get cold(er) while he brought out something else.
Quite honestly, the cook should have been embarrassed to put these diaper scrapings on a customer's plate.  The waiter should have refused to bring it out.  The waiter should have warned me when I ordered the stuff what they were delivering.
The waiter delivered bare-minimum service, did the slightest possible to try to "remedy" my vegetable dilemma. 
As an aside, note the blood-red morsel at the bottom of the plate.  That was the "medium rare" steak.  It was good, despite the cow mooing in protest as I ate her.  But I guess that's what I get when I correct the waiter when he repeated my medium-rare order as "medium well".
On the plus side, my wife enjoyed her salad.  
Store 1366... just wait until I fill out my survey!  And if the waiter wants to know why he got a $0 tip... maybe someone at Corporate can explain.'

b'I have to say I generally like your restaurant however,  this past Friday (5/08/15) we did not have a good experience. My cousin who just moved from PR to Florida wanted to visit your restaurant, so we went. We waited over 30 minutes to sit when there were plenty of tables available.  I asked the host what was taking so long and she said to have a seat because other people were in front of me. We then waited for over 15 minutes to have someone come and serve us our drinks and this is not  counting the time it took to even get a waiter. When we get our drinks, they forget to bring my husband\'s beer. We order our meal and when we finally got our meals it had been over an hour. The food was warm,  and the orders were messed up. We finally called the manager because we were so hungry and they wanted to take my cousin\'s meal so they can "fix it". They gave her ribs instead of a steak.  The manager fixed the meals but didn\'t even discounted us for the inconvenience. Between our party we paid over  $130 for the worst experience ever.  Even though I was upset I still tipped the waitress but needless to say won\'t be visiting your restaurant for a while. Not a good first impression for my cousin who had heard so many wonderful things about your restaurant. Below is a picture of the restaurant and all the available tables just in our section alone.   #disappointed'

b'On attending your restaurant in Macquarie Centre NSW Australia, I had expected a decent meal. 
I decided to order the buffalo chicken burritos. Feeling relatively full after one burrito I took the second home. 
It was to my disbelief and displeasure that that evening I was horribly ill, vomiting and shaking, between the hours of 11pm to 2am. Salmonella poisoning is what I expected it was. Yet, when I went to open up the leftovers this morning I was shocked to see mould had grown from, not the chicken but the SAUCE. 
I am thoroughly disappointed and will not be returning to either tgifridays in Australia or any other location. 
I sincerely hope you will solve this issue so that future customers do not experience the same problem.'

b'Today my other half and I stopped at your concord nh location. Which I might add we often do. Today was the worst experience I have ever had in any restaurant. Our waitress was very slow and confused, she placed our order as well as other customers orders around us wronge. She did apologise, however, when we received our appetizer we had no plates or utensils. After trying to get her attention several times she finally came over. I asked for plates and utensils, she brought us 2 plates and 2 sets of utensils, even,though we had our 1 year old daughter with us. Every time food or drinks where delivered to the table it was put within reach of our daughter (compromising her safety with hot food ). Even,after all this when our meals where delivered they where wronge, we sent them back. When they came out a second time , mine was suppose to be the jack daniels rib eye cooked medium with mashed and broccoli. The stake was more then well done and mashed potatoes where cold and inedible. His all American burger was so salty he could not eat it. My daughters food was stone cold. Part way tgrough eating my rubber stake i found human hair on it. I immediately asked the waitress for the manager because I was honestly furious by this point. I was told a manager was unavailable. The pictures of the food and table where taken right before we left. None of us could stomach the food. I was astonished that when we received our bill we where expected to pay for it all. Im sorry but if you value your reputation as a business you need to get someone in there that is capable of running a restaurant. Someone who will take care of your customers, as a business owner myself I would be appalled if this was how my employees where running things, not only comprising the health and well being but down right just not caring. P.s the ribs you see are part of the first order they made the mistake on. I asked her to remive them from my table, she didnt. So when i realised how terrible my meal was i tried one, and it was the consistency of saw dust.... Hope this helps you fix one of my favorite restaurants in the area'

b'I went to TGI Fridays Wolfchase in Memphis about two years ago and ordered the Parmesan chicken and mashed potatoes however never returned due to the lack of customer service and on top of that, a raw chicken breast. I told myself I would NEVER go back and stayed true to my word until I came downtown Memphis today for a conference. My first issue with my visit today was the very terrible lack of customer service and one server assigned to a table with 10 people. It took literally 30 minutes to get WATERS that we ordered with lemon. Then another hour to get FOOD! Ok I understand it will take a little longer to get food with a larger table but when I wait an hour and the food comes out COLD something is NOT right about that!! One of my sisters and I ordered chicken tenders for the meal with salads and a side. To start, my chicken tenders compared to my sisters tenders looked microwaved! While hers were fried! I ate a piece of the tip from the chicken tenders before ripping it open and noticing that my chicken tenders were RAW! Straight RAW! I could not believe it. (btw my sisters tenders were still frozen inside.) Anyways, I was so disgusted and shocked! What made it worse is that no manager or anyone else came to the table to apologize and try to make it right. The server brought me a ticket and said "they took the tenders off, now only the drink is on there." I was not paying for ANYTHING! Don\'t give me raw food and then try to bill me for anything!! That is Crazy!! This is the second time this has happened to me. Second time is a charm because I will NOT be back!! I will write reviews everywhere. Word of mouth is everything. Oh and did I mention that when I went into the bathroom I had to ask for soap and paper towels?! So imagine all the workers that used the restroom without washing their hands and preparing your food!! Exactly!! Do not go here!!!'

b'I would like to share an experience I had at one of your restaurants.....below is the story....the folks involved were from store 0807...the server was Rebecca and the manager was Leah....they will never know how much their kindness meant to me!\nThe most amazing thing happened to me today....myself and my co-worker Pierre-Luc are travelling through Dallas airport and we stopped at the TGI Fridays in the airport....the manager on duty saw Pierre-luc\'s bag and realized we were military...she sent the server over to ask us if we are...and when we said yes...she said...well we have a discount for you folks I will see what I have...and walked away. A little while later the manager came back with a 25.00 gift certificate and said they had raised money before Christmas to give to the military folks...and she thanked us for our service...I said "But we are Canadian military" to which she came back with...."you are military". Tell me that is not the coolest thing ever!! They totally made made my day...and if it hadn\'t been for Pierre-Luc teasing me...I may have shed a tear.....my pride in being military rang strong today. So if you are ever near this airport please stop in at the TGI Fridays near gate 30... Store 0807 and have a drink...or a bite to eat....they deserve your business!! I am attaching a picture of the gift card (sorry it is not clear)....is that not the coolest thing! Bless their amazing hearts!'

b'Editor Vebj\xc3\xb8rn Selbekk, who was tormented by the Norwegian government for reprinting the Danish cartoons way back when, and who has since been a leading voice in Norway for freedom of speech, was to have been interviewed by Dagbladet today and chose to meet the reporter at a TGI Friday's in Oslo. "It's my favorite restaurant," he explains. "I feel like it's a bit of a political statement every time I eat there -I'm striking back at anti-Americanism." But when the TGIF manager saw the Dagbladet photographer and asked what the story was about, he refused to allow the interview to be conducted in his establishment. Selbekk was disappointed: "This is an American restaurant. 'Land of the free, home of the brave,' Americans sing. This wasn't very brave. It was simply cowardly."

I ate at TGI Friday's in Oslo just last week. No more.

b'I had the worst "dining" experience of my life at TGIFridays (well there's your first mistake). The waiter took our orders, but not the menus, and 35 minutes later our appetizers arrived. There was no soy sauce for the pot stickers, but I could manage. Now it was time for the main course... Of the 9 meals ordered, 3 came out correct. 

My broccoli was on the plate, but in a plastic bag. You know how it is, some places are all about the presentation. We still haven't received the shipping confirmation on Alicia's fries, but the waiter was kind enough to offer to remove the undelivered fries and Steve's undelivered beer from the check. I guess we all know what happened at this point with our dessert order.

This was all of course before he decided to head home for the night. Once realizing he left the manager took over. I did feel bad for the guy with every table complaining, but splitting our tables bill and taking $40 off of $200 worth of food wasn't enough. 

Point of the story... I gave my first tip below 20%, and it was 0%.'

b"Ate at the Orange, CT location last night. I ordered the sriracha chicken loaded potatoes. The first batch came out 1.5 potato skins later I found a 1 inch long blue rubberband in it. The wait staff promptly took the plate away and within a few minutes were out with another one. The waiter was very apologetic which was nice. I decided to use a fork and knife to eat the next one to pick through for a rubberband. This time I found a hunk of mystery meat that was still raw. The waiter came over immediately and grabbed the manager. The manager quickly took the piece of meat and went into the kitchen with it. He came back out and said he really had no idea what it was. I said it looks like pork or dark meat chicken. He said it looks like pork to him. I explained to him that for religious reasons I can't eat pork. He said no no no its chicken let me double check. He came back out and basically said it's not really our problem because we just have everything shipped to us and we heat it up. They took it off the bill and I had to ask for a sprite for free. the manager never came back out and the waiter still super apologetic admitted that they were pretty sure it was pork. I was up most of the night with severe stomach pain and nausea. I will never ever go back to any location."

b'Honestly one of the worst experiences I have ever experienced. b'In the past we always went to the TGI Fridays next to the movie theater after catching a movie.  Tonight has totally changed that.  First, I had a stripes reward to use.  It was late and I forgot to tell the waitress before ordering.  I got the 2 for $16 deal and my son got new york bacon burger.  I remembered the reward and got her attention and told her.  She said "You can't use that on 2 for 16".  Since i had just placed my order, i asked if i could change it, she said "NO" and it seemed she was trying NOT to accommodate me.  I then asked if I could use it for my son's meal.  She said "No because it would have had to be rung up on separate tickets."   I told her to ring it up separate and she finally complied. 
 ATTITUDE MUCH?  

Then, when my son was ALMOST done eating....he had a few fries left and a waitress walking by grabbed his plate and took the rest of his fries without asking if he was done.

The final straw came when I took a bite of my sandwich and it literally tasted like feces.  I spit it right back out while trying not to vomit at the taste in my mouth.  

The only positive thing I can say is that the cost of the sandwich was taken off my bill.  No way was I eating that!

BAD, EXTREMELY BAD EXPERIENCE AT THE ORANGE PARK MALL LOCATION IN ORANGE PARK, FL.'

b'FALSE ADVERTISING!!!  
Here's the specials according to the TGIF Official Website; however, if you ask the server at the Humble, TX location, he will tell you this special ENDED!  

Upon being seated, we inquired about the 1/2 price appetizers and we were told they were NOT available because the special and ended and was replaced with the endless appetizer special.  He showed us the printed material that he had to retrieve from another table because the information from the book on our table was missing the "specials info".  He showed us that the 1/2 price appetizer special wasn't listed, only the endless appetizer menu was available as the special.  We ordered ours appetizers according to what the waiter offered.  After ordering, I went on the website from my phone, and listed below is was I found.

I was right, on Wednesday, TGIF has 1/2 price appetizers!  I showed it to the waiter and he said, "Let me ask the manager."   The waiter came back with ANOTHER menu booklet and GUESS WHAT?...The 1/2 price appetizer special for Wednesday was listed!  LOL. THEN, the waiter said, "Oh, you're right, it is 1/2 price appetizers on Wednesday, but I'm sorry, you have to sit in the BAR area to receive that special!  

Are you serious?  Who trains these waiters?  From the moment we sat down, the waiter couldn't clearly tell us what the specials were.  So, you figure, the manager might make good on the special price since CLEARLY, if the waiter had answered our question about the special, we could have MOVED to the BAR AREA!!!

Instead, the manager decided to make 3 loyal customers angry, lost money on the food that was ordered, (probably cooked and ready to be delivered by the time we canceled our order), and comped the buffalo wings appetizer that came out WAY before the other appetizers did. 

OH, I guess we can figure out who trained the WAITER that doesn't  know what specials are available...it's the MANAGER!!  So, I guess we need to ask, who trained the MANAGER?  PATHETIC CUSTOMER SERVICE at the HUMBLE, TEXAS location!  I was in food service as a F&B for 15 years! Is this how the companies are teaching their managers how to handle customer  complaints?  It seems this situation cost the company WAY more than it should have!  

A VERY UNSATISFIED CUSTOMER!

'
link_name: b'Daily Specials | TGI Fridays Casual Dining Restaurant & Bar'

b"Can you believe this?? We went for an enjoyable meal at the Poughkeepsie location of TGI Friday's to watch the World Cup finals - Germany vs. Argentina. This is what happened: 
1. Our bartender told us that we couldn't share our endless appetizers even though there was flagrant sharing by others. That level of inconsistency is annoying when you're trying to follow the rules. 
2. They had run out of boneless buffalo wings. When I confronted the manager, he admitted that he had run out and had to substitute with 'a non-TGI Friday's product'. We don't even know what we've been eating! He apologized and said that he had been wiped out of stock by a team of Marist athletes. Instead of taking them off the menu, he made the switch without informing his patrons. He didn't even offer to absorb the cost given his deception. Do these look like nuggets to you?
"

Distinctly average to poor food. Waitress asked if everything was ok at end of meal - we explained we wernt impressed at all and she just said " oh " and walked off with no offer of rectifying it and we couldn\'t be bothered to press the point. b'I went TGI Fridays with my husband and son to take advantage of your two for $10 special, since we have seen the commercials on TV. We asked our server about the deal, since it was not on any menu, it took her ten minutes to hunt down a "menu" which is posted below. It upsets me to know that your company does not want us to know about your specials and specifically tell your servers not to mention it (see number 4).Then you go on to tell them that if the customer does know about the special then make sure you know what is on that menu.(see number 5). Why not just include it in the normal menu? Or perhaps a flyer placed on table? Its better than having a special that is only available to the lucky few that happened to see the commercial.I love TGIFridays. My sister would bring me there every weekend before she passed away, and my memories there were always fun, but this leaves a sour taste in my mouth. I wish the server would have read the disclaimer at the top and never let me see it.'

b'NEVER BUY A TGI FRIDAYS GIFT CARD THEY CAN BE A SCAM. My girlfriend's mom bought us what she thought was a $25 gift card from Giant Eagle Pittsburgh and when we used it at TGI FRIDAYS KING OF PRUSSIA MALL, PA there was only a balance of $14.81.  The manager at that store was completely rude and did not even attempt to help find out how this could have happened and just told us to try calling the back of the card because it would "take him a month to look up the transaction information".  We sat in the restaurant and called the 1-888-284-5544 (back of gift card number) and they could only tell us the STORE ID where the card was used (which was useless because she couldn't tell me where the location was).  

The manager at the KOP location was completely useless...thankfully his waiter was a little more caring and at least attempted to help us.  Will be calling the Giant Eagle as well as the TGI Fridays customer relations number in the morning.  I CANNOT BELIEVE TGI FRIDAYS WOULD NOT MAKE IT A REQUIREMENT FOR STORES SELLING THEIR PRODUCT TO PROTECT THEIR GIFT CARDS BEHIND SOME KIND OF SECURITY!! IT'S LIKE LEAVING CASH ON THE SHELVES AND NOT BOTHERING TO PROTECT IT.

b"This was the response I got after e-mailing your company about a horrible experience I had at your Bowie, MD location. We waited forever for service, then when I inquired about foods that didn't have soy/dairy due to an allergy in my daughter, who I breastfeed, I was treated as though I were insane for even asking a question like that. I was never offered a menu with allergy information, the waitress never even offered to go ask the cooks about the foods I was questioning, she just said she wasn't sure if the foods had soy/dairy. I ordered the pretzels because I thought they may be safe, but they came out with what appeared to be butter all over them. It took me another 15 minutes to get the waitresses attention to ask her if they could make me the pretzels without the butter, another 15 minutes later the pretzels were brought to me but by this time everyone in my party was done eating and my appetite was fading away. I ate the pretzels and they were okay, but my daughter was up sick all night with a tummy ache/diarrhea so apparently the preztels were not safe. I did not appreaciate this e-mail, the typo was the icing on the cake. The person did not even acknowledge my complaints or even appologize. I used to go to your restaurants for happy hour before I was a mother but I will not be returning. Allergies are a very serious issue a"

b'Am I surprised that TGI Friday\'s was just voted #2 for worst restaurants in America by Men\'s Health? Not in the least. A few weeks ago, Sky and I were between flights in Dallas. Famished, we stopped into the airport\'s TGI Friday\'s. To my complete surprise, they now have a few more vegetarian options on the menu*. I happily ordered the black bean burger and didn\'t expect much. What I did get was far more than I had bargained for: \r\n1,160 calories, 17g sat fat (RDA is 20g PER DAY), 3400mg of sodium (!) and 71g of fat. Are you KIDDING me?! I ask, how is this even LEGAL?! A while back I lowered my sodium intake to 1,500mg per day. This ONE sandwich provided me with over two days worth of sodium. I am honestly surprised I did not drop dead on my way to the terminal. Thanks for nothing, Friday\'s. We will not be back!\r\n* "We happily try to accommodate any special requests and try to make substitutions for vegetarian creations (though no meal is vegetarian certified)" - Taken from the nutrition section of Friday\'s website. Again, thanks for nothing!'

b"I have to say, we've been going to our local T.G.I.Friday's for the past few years with wonderful results. It's one of our kids' favorite places, and ours too. However, we went there last night for my birthday dinner and I was somewhat disappointed. We've always had good meals, hot & fresh food, just always enjoyed it. But last night, when I received my normal sizzling chicken and cheese, the mashed potatoes were ice cold. I said something, and yes, they brought me new, hot potatoes. And then I started eating the chicken and it was quite tough and not juicy or fresh at all. I know, I could have just complained last night, but it was my birthday, and I'm dealing with one of my kids having been in the hospital for the past 5+ weeks, so I just wasn't in the mood. I'm sure we'll go back, because my kids still like the restaurant. I still wanted to say something, because it bummed me out after I thought about it more. b"Some coworkers and I went to T.G.I. Friday's in Brick, New Jersey today and found the service and food to be fair below our expectations.  Our server was inattentive, and when we tried to call him over at one point to ask whether our chips and salsa was coming out soon (we had been waiting thirty minutes at this point) he actually acknowledged us, started to approach us, then turned around and walked away for an extended time.  We asked a server, not our own, about refills and our chips and she informed us that she would ask our server.  We had to ask a total of three times before chips or refills came.  Our chips ended up coming out with our food forty minutes after we ordered.  Most of us noticed our food was cold, or not cooked to their desired doneness.  The avocados on my Sedona Black Bean Burger were the size of match sticks and looked bruised and some of the onions were papery.  We never saw a manager to comment on the food, nor did our server ask how we liked our food.    When it came time to pay the bill, he had charged one of my coworkers twice for her drink, which was supposed to be free refills.  I would understand this kind of service if it was busy at the restaurant, but there was barely anyone there and we saw him go to all the surrounding tables but avoided ours, especially after he saw we were becoming agitated.  No apology was offered for the late chips, nor was their an explanation as to why he walked away from us.  I'm sorry to say I do not plan on going back to T.G.I. Friday's."

b'I feel the need to share my experience with the TGI Friday\'s in Pittsburgh Pa behind the Consol Energy Center:  \r\nToday was the second time in 2 months that a group of us from work went to Friday\'s for lunch.  Both times we had the same waitress \xe2\x80\x93 Cynthia. The first trip (mid-November) she was very rude and VERY slow.  It took us 45 min to get our meals (we all ordered soup and salad). When the food finally came, someone said that we have to pack up b/c we only get an hour for lunch, to which she said, "Well, I guess you better eat fast".  RUDE!  I can understand delays if you\xe2\x80\x99re new or it is really busy (which it wasn\xe2\x80\x99t) But there is no reason to be rude and abrasive like that.  Today, we went and it took her 15 min to come take our orders, she did not bring us drinks until after our appetizers came. She also did not bring out enough straws and coasters, ever. Our food was very good.  We gave her our payments and when she brought back the folders, she had charged my card for the person next to me and that person the person next to her.  The man next to me got charged for both mine and his meal.  Then, when we pointed it out SHE BLAMED US! Saying we handed it to her together and wrong.  REALLY?!? We each handed her a slip and a card, how did we mess it up?  She ended up charging my bank account twice before the manager helped her void the entire order.  We still do not know who paid for whose lunch or even if we paid at all.  We did not leave a tip and do not plan on going to that Friday\xe2\x80\x99s EVER again!'

b"Normally love my T.G.I. Friday's but today was the second time at the one at Consol Energy Center in downtown Pittsburgh 15219 that the entire lunch trip was a complete disaster from the service to the mis-payment of all the checks.  

Drink orders were never taken until 25 min once seated (was not busy - 11:30am) and taken with our meal orders.  The food was fine at least.  The waitress (which was the second time we had her for our group of 9) took an extended amount of time coming back to the table and never brought out enough coasters or straws for everyone seated - and never did.  

Once it was time to pay (separate checks), everyone was charged the wrong check at our table.  Then, it was a hassle to rectify the problem on behalf of the waitress AND the Manager who was less than willing to help.  He was very stand-offish.  We still do not know if our credit accounts were credited properly - will know in a couple days once updated by the banking system.  We asked to have our purchases voided and credited and then re-charged - which they did not give us evidence of this.  So no one knows what they paid for their lunch or how much.

Unfortunately, we will not be going back to this T.G.I. Friday's and have shared our experiences with our co-workers.  This was the second time in less than 6 months that we had horrible service at this one.  We won't try a third.

I know not all of your restaurants have this horrible service but something definitely needs changed at this one - especially when it is a larger party involved.  I love the Greensburg, PA one but will definitely take note if I am there with a larger party going forward."

b'I argued with my friend to go to the Elmira, NY TGIF over another restaurant for dinner last night and it turned out to be an awful visit. We were seated by a booth near the bar. We understand that it was a later dinner and people at the bar are drinking and having a good time. However, that\'s no reason to disturb others around them. There were a few (2-3) men at the bar who seemed to know the bartender as well as the waitresses/waiters. They were obviously inebriated and out of control and none of the staff seemed to have a problem with it...instead they were talking and dancing with them right next to our table while we were trying to eat! Another group that was sitting behind us got up to leave and made a comment to the men and a verbal altercation took place...lewd and vulgar language was used which is ABSOLUTELY unecessary in a "family friendly" restaurant. What bothered me the most was that the restaurant staff took no responsibility for the obnoxious behavior for these people...instead they egged them on telling them that the customer was out of line for saying something!!! Our waitress included did not apologize to us for such a terrible dinner. I\'m still appalled that the staff or manager did not step in to rectify the situation. Please train your staff...there are people that would love to have a job and would do it right. There are MANY other good and respectable places to eat...next time I will be listening to my friend and going with his choice. VERY DISAPPOINTED. '

b"I object to your ad. Even though I myself don't believe the world will come to an end this month, I know many who do, and others who are torn apart by the fear that this may be real. One young woman I know is terrified and depressed and can barely get out of bed each morning for school and work, as she counts the days.

I am a behavioral therapist working to help people struggling with phobias and OCD. Their lives are wracked enough with fear, doubt and worry. To have one of their favorite restaurants thinking it's funny capitalizing on this terror is unthinkable and cruel. I'm a regular at my local Friday's and I earn stripes all the time. But now I'm not sure I ever want to eat at your place again.

Think about this and please retract your ad. Apologizing to the many who are in fear might also be appropriate.

-:\xc2\xa6:-Warren Barlowe, Behavioral Therapist; Long Island OCD-:\xc2\xa6:-
"
b"Friday's\xc2\xae End-of-the-World Survival Guide Page #27"

b"I love going to TGI FRIDAYS with family & friends, and typically I thoroughly enjoy my visit. Unfortunately today I had a horrible dining experience @ the Fowler Ave location in Tampa FL. First we were rushed by the waitress to place our order. Then when we made a small change to our order before the appetizers came out, the waitress got an attitude & rushed off. She only came back with 1 menu. It took forever to bring out the appetizers, & then our entrees came a couple minutes later. When the Parmesan Crusted Chicken came out it was dry, & when my Skillet Garlic Shrimp came out it was ok but the shrimp still had the tails on them. That was odd to me because most dishes have the tails removed. When asking for the take out containers & the check, the waitress sent out someone else with the containers & no check. Then when we asked again she acted like she didn't hear us & kept walking. I wouldn't recommend that location to ANYONE!  I'm VERY disappointed. "

b"Hi there. I wanted to bring to light a situation that I am currently dealing with, as I have been ignored up until now (Case #3282196). On September 4, I wrote an email to TGI Fridays customer service about my recent visit - in short, poor service, poor food (not to mention the wrong food was brought out and our waitress didn't come to our table for over 15 minutes). I was promised that management would contact me to resolve the situation - over a month later, I still had not heard anything, so I wrote another letter - the manager left me a message while I was at work, said he'd call me again the next day since he didn't get ahold of me, and said he'd be sending out compensation for the visit that afternoon. He never called again, didn't send anything, and haven't heard back since. It has now been over two months and I am still left wondering what happened. I'm incredibly disappointed with the lack of response this has generated, let alone the false promises made to me by the manager. I truly wish your CEO could read this and see the damage that you're doing - perhaps you need better training with your guest relations, but so far, I have encountered nothing but disappointment. "

b"I am writing to express how disappointed I am at the quality of food that was provided last night when I took my family to what was suppose to be a nice dinner.  I overpaid for mediocre food! The chicken fingers tasted like frozen tyson chicken nuggets and she refused to eat it.  My husband ordered a burger with fries and it was overall sloppy and the lettuce was brown and wilted.  My husband waited another 10 minutes for ketchup and the waitress brought out ketchup packets.  If I wanted McDonald's quality food and service that is where we would've gone but I was trying to treat my family to something nicer, which I regret.  My experience at the TGI Fridays on Rt3 in Clifton NJ was horrible.  The establishment was very busy and I didn't have the energy to sit and complain and argue about the quality of the food and service and that is why i am writing today.  I regret not taking a picture of my daughters chicken fingers.  It was disgusting!"

b"I am hoping TGI Fridays can help! On August 25 our good friend Kevin was hospitalized after a blockage and improperly functioning pancreas caused his kidneys, lungs, and other organs to fail. He has undergone several surgeries and has been placed in a medically induced coma. He continues to make positive steps towards recovery, however it is not known how long it will take to heal. 

Kevin has always been there for anyone that needed help, and now it's our turn to help him. Kevin recently switched careers, and did not have health insurance at the time. He still has a long road ahead of him, and the bills will continue to add up. All proceeds from this benefit will go to his medical bills, lost wages, and treatments. 

We are hoping that you can help by providing a donation that we can auction off at the benefit. Please let me know if you are willing to make a contribution. Official letters of request and/or flyers can be provided. 

Thank you in advance for any help you may be able to offer."

b'Hey Fridays, I have a complaint/suggestion about your rewards program. I think when you earn a reward, it should be treated as a true REWARD and not a coupon. It\'s not fair that if I want to use my reward, then no one else at my table can use any coupons or pick-2/pick-3 deals. I did the math last time and our meal ended up costing MORE money using the "reward" than it would have without it (and that\'s just for two people eating, usually I go to Fridays in a group). What is the incentive to earn stripes and earn rewards if you end up WASTING MONEY to use them? Most people do not go to Fridays to eat alone, so it\'s really unfair to not allow the other customers at the table to take part in the value deals just because one person has a reward. I have a ton of stripes racked up but I may never get to use them. Doesn\'t really make me want to go to Fridays anymore. :('

b"I have been meaning to post this because I am so amazed by this company. My husband is active duty Air Force and while traveling this summer (8-2-12) we stopped off in Omaha, NE to visit the Zoo. While there we decided to grab some take out and called TGIF. There are five people in my family so the order was quite large. They advised us the order would be ready in about 15 minutes. So my husband and my oldest son went to pick up order When my husband arrived he was given the bill. He politley asked them if they gave a military discount. The young lady at the counter said they did and said she needed to get athorization from her manager. After a couple of minutes she returned and said our bill was taken care of. Now this was $61.00 in food. My husband asked several times if they were sure. She said yes, his service to our country was payment enough so they generously gave him the food for free. Imagine the surprise on his face!!! He thanked them for their generousity and handed the hostess a nice tip. I have been meaning to thank them for what they did. Never have we been given so much from a restaraunt. This was the coolest thing and it will never be forgetton. I cannot rememeber the names of the individuals, but the restraunt was by Regency Street, in the mall area. So THANK YOU for your kindness and hsopitality!!!! We will be sure to let people know how honored we were!!!\nFrom the Mitchell's in South Dakota. "

b'Clearly my comments aren\'t reaching the appropriate departments from my previous experiences, if its not bad service its bad food at the Moline, Illinois location, Today my husband and I ate there and did the 2 for $15.99 meals, my food was alright, my appetizer was by far the highlight of my meal, as I went to move my parm fries around I found a dead fly or some kind of a bug that looked similar to it, I told my server and he sent his manager over, I was given two options he could remake it all (didn\'t want to wait for another well done steak to be cooked-considering I had a very antsy and tired 4 year old who wasn\'t going to sit still not to mention I kinda lost my appetite after finding a dead fly in my food) or that he would take care of it, he "took care of it" by taking the steak meal off of my bill and charged me full price for my appetizer, which was  8.99... so instead of getting the two for 15.99 deal we got $6 off our bill.. I don\'t see how that justifies it, maybe they are used to having dead flies in their food, I\'m not sure.. This is not my first bad experience there, however this will be my last I will not return there no matter what, I\'m tempted to dispute the amount on my credit card, however majority of it was paid on a gift card given to us as a gift.  I\'ve gotten horrible service, under cooked food, and other times the food and service is great, I\'ve complained online, and had their general manager call me back before, I\'m not looking for free food, I\'d take a refund.  But i will not return to that location again, I have over 200 stripe points on my account we eat there whenever we are in the area for local shows at the arena next door, so unless Iowa City gets a TGIFridays I guess those will also go to waste.   You are more than welcome to message me back for further information, maybe having this posted where everyone will see it will bring some attention to this matter. '

b"The service provided to our group of 8 was below average throughout our entire visit. My wife's Wedge Salad was not brought to her until her meal came out while everyone elses appetizers were brought out before their meal. Our drinks were all empty as we ate and we had to ask a kitchen employee who was by our area watching T.V. to please contact our waitress so that she may get us more drinks since she was not checking in with us to see if we needed anything else and NEVER brought out glasses of water that a few of us ordered as well as one of our sides of corn that came with one of our meals. We complained to a manager that we did not feel that the 18% Gratuity should be added to our bill since there was MINIMAL effort on our waitresses part to make sure our visit and meal was enjoyable. He stated that it was policy to add this to parties of 8 or more and forced us to pay it and didn't even offer us a solution or compensation to our unsatisfactory visit! This is by far the worst experience at a Restaurant and in no way is an acceptable way to treat a customer who had a legitimate complaint about the service. I, as well as our group of friends, plan on never returning to any TGI Fridays restaurants any time soon since we have been shown that not all of your customers are as valued as your nationally televised commercials lead people to believe!\n\nTGI Fridays #1116 at: 7221 East Carson Blvd. Long Beach, CA 90808 \xe2\x80\x94 "

b'I have  been frequenting T.G.I. Friday\'s for years, and for the most part I have received good customer service. I am a teacher and my colleagues and I like doing some of our planning at TGIF because of the lay back atmosphere. However, last night  at the TGIF in North Miami Beach, my girl friends and I received despicable customer service.  The waiter (Irvence) was rude,  and sarcastic and unapologetic for his lackluster service. He got our orders wrong, and blamed us for not getting it right. Moreover, when we tried to complain to the  manager (kevin) and dispute the gratuity charges that we felt he didn\'t deserve,  he too didn\'t apologize for the  poor service we  received but bolstered the poor actions of the waiter by making a racial comment in a condescending tone: "okay what do you want? Do guys want something for free". Assuming  that because we were black we wanting something for free. Then, he calls an off duty police officer to "monitor" us. At that moment, I changed from a loyal  patron of your establishment  to  feeling criminalized because I was unsatisfied with horrible service. It  was thus far, the  most deprecating and humiliating experience of my life. No human being should feel that way when trying to enjoy their hard earned money. I WILL NEVER patronize any of your restaurants. #SODISAPPOINTED'

b'Last night I was almost arrested because I chose to speak up against the horrible service at your establishment.  I am a licensed attorney in the State of Florida and I specialize in criminal law.  I spoke to two managers about the atrocious service from Irvins the sarcastic waiter.  I thought managers were supposed to be neutral parties who listen to the customers.  That never happened! Kevin came to our table and told us that they could not help us and insinuated that we were trying to get out of our Happy Hour bill. I asked to speak to another manager and Kevin go talks to an officer.  The officer then stands over our shoulder and told me that he was going to arrest me because I was talking about the poor customer service.  I will never go to TGIFridays again! I have over 2000 followers on my social networks and I will let them all know about my horrible experience.  I would welcome the opportunity to speak with you all about my experience and suggestions as to how to improve the cornerstone of every business . . . customer service.  '

b"Maybe with some public exposure, our complaint will finally get some attention!
We like the food. We really LIKE the food. Service is great and so is the staff. Great meal deals and discounts, too.
We won't go to this restaurant anymore because no matter how many times we've gone there, we freeze our butts off! It's cold and it's drafty. We ALWAYS have to ask them - no matter what time of year it is - to turn up the heat. We're tired of asking. They keep it cold to keep the staff comfortable. If you're a customer and you're cold, well, get over yourself. If there's a warm spot in the place, they either don't know where it is or aren't interested in seating us there. The rest of my family doesn't eat here anymore for the same reason.
I've complained before. A LOT. I'm done complaining. There's way too many other places to eat in the DFW area to put up with this.

Craig Nelson
DeSoto, TX
nelsoncraigf@aol.com"

b'Hi, I was in THIS Fridays the last night eating wings with extra Jack Sauce (MMMM DELICIOUS) and the waitress told me that the way I was eating was offending other customers. I was merely lickingr my fingers. I had recently gone through a break up and frankly didn\'t care how I looked, or whether I had Jack Sauce covering my face, or, as the waitress put it, "was being a deplorable slob". Friday\'s is a place I can go to be alone and get away from everyone, and this offended me. Is there an official TGI Fridays table manner handbook? I don\'t wanna lose my special place.'

b'My husband & I, and our 3 children, arrived at 5:50.  (I know the exact time, because I received a text in the waiting area.)  We waited there for about 10 minutes before being seated in the empty restaurant.  We wanted a table, but we were seated in a cramped booth in a corner.  

There was a spray bottle of cleaning solution on one of the seats.  The was completely confused.  Then, we noticed drink spills on our table.  The host was still dumbfounded.  The waiter brought napkins for US to clean up the spills from the previous guests.  We handed him the bottle of cleaning solution that was in our way.  We then noticed food residue all over the table.  The server took one of our napkins to wipe up the food, that spray bottle was never used.  

The server (Alan) wanted to take our order right away.  We told him we needed a couple minutes to look over the menus.   He came back 20 minutes later.  We even had to wave down another server that we were more than ready to order.

We were supposed to have complimentary chips.  We asked for them 3 different times before we got them.   When the chips eventually came, we had seven (7) chips on a large plate with a big bowl of salsa.  The chips were very hard and very greasy.   

My husband and I eventually received our first course.  Our kids still had nothing but the hard chips that they wanted nothing to do with. My daughter was given water, instead of Sprite.  My other daughter never got a lemonade refill after multiple requests.

We saw people around us seated AFTER us, eat and leave before we even got our food.  I brought this all to the manager's attention.  Unbelievably, the bartender was even yelling to the manager that he couldn't believe we haven't been served yet, because he saw us sitting there so long with no food.  

The manager asked me, "What do you want me to do to fix this?"  I asked him what he THINKS he should do to fix this.  At this time, we saw the server bringing our food.  The manager told me and my husband that he would come visit us later to see how things are.

HE NEVER VISITED US!  If he did, I would have pointed out to him that my husband NEVER received his meal.  Eventually, the server shows up to ask how our food is.  My husband told him, "How would I know?  I haven't received my food yet?"  The server's response was, "Sorry boss... I'll go get your food."  

This was the final straw!  It was now 7:30, and we had had enough.  I went looking for the manager again, but he was nowhere to be found.  We explained to the host, who was at the door, that we were leaving and not paying.  

That was THE MOST horrible restaurant visit I have ever experienced!'

b"My family's tradition for years has been going to TGI Friday's for NYE.  So, we'll be there again tomorrow.  I need to know what your vegetarian options are.  After looking at the menu yet again (after being told there would be vegetarian options), what a surprise that there are none.  So, yet again, 3 out of the 5 people going to have nothing to eat but mozzarella sticks (and, mind you, one of those people is lactose intolerant, so the cheese doesn't really go well).  If you aren't going to offer vegetarian options, you should at least reduce the price if we take the meat out of the pasta or salad dishes (the meat makes up most of the price anyway, so why should I pay for something I'm taking out).  We used to go to TGI Friday's all the time, but now only go for NYE only because it's a tradition.  We've debated going other places, but it's too painful to break tradition.  At least offer veggie burgers!  Almost every other restaurant does, so I'm not sure why you don't.  I'm not sure how much longer we'll keep up the tradition, though, if you don't offer vegetarian options because it's not something we look forward to anymore.  Applebee's is right around the corner for us and they have more options, so we may be there next year if options aren't available.  However, I'd love to know what your choices are for now since we'll be there tomorrow."

b"I have been a longtime fan of Friday's, in fact, was a member of the original Friday's points program. The program ended and I lost a large lump sum of points. This seems to be the norm with points programs from banks to grocery stores. Since points are earned by spending, it is like stealing when they are ended with no reimbursement. What's worse is when given a chance to spend points being sent to an off-the-wall web site where you can get a little trinket for an outrages amount of points, plus shipping. So please, if (when) this points program ends show customer courtesy and refund the points in a practical, appreciative manner."
